---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import SectionWrapper from '../components/SectionWrapper.astro';
import CTAButton from '../components/CTAButton.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Joshua Wilson"
  description="Auckland-based data professional with 12 years experience across 8+ sectors."
>
  <Hero
    hasHeadshot
    headshot="/images/headshot-suit.jpg"
    headline="Joshua Wilson"
    subline="Data Professional. Auckland, New Zealand."
    bg="var(--color-linen)"
  />

  <SectionWrapper narrow>
    <p>
      Most organisations are sitting on answers they haven't found yet. The data exists. The
      signals are there. What's missing is someone willing to look honestly at what it says —
      and say it clearly, even when it's inconvenient.
    </p>
    <p>
      That's the work I've been doing since 2014. Twelve years across healthcare, government,
      agriculture, real estate, energy, and more. The industries change. The problem doesn't:
      data that isn't used is just cost.
    </p>
    <p>
      I'm not interested in building reports for their own sake. I'm interested in the moment a
      leadership team sees something they couldn't see before — and decides to act on it.
    </p>
  </SectionWrapper>

  <SectionWrapper narrow>
    <p>
      That obsession with surfacing what's hidden led me to build something. DeepWeave is a
      business process visibility platform — a direct product of that same question applied to
      operational data.
    </p>
    <CTAButton href="/deepweave" label="More about DeepWeave" />
  </SectionWrapper>

  <SectionWrapper>
    <div class="closing-cta">
      <CTAButton href="mailto:joshua@joshuawilson.co.nz" label="Book a consultation" />
    </div>
  </SectionWrapper>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  p + p {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  p + a,
  p + .cta {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    display: inline-block;
  }

  .closing-cta {
    text-align: center;
  }
</style>
